message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Canada in the past five years is the legalization of recreational cannabis. On October 17, 2018, Canada became the second country in the world, after Uruguay, to legalize the recreational use of marijuana nationwide. This event had a significant impact on various aspects of Canadian society, including legal, social, economic, and health-related factors. The legalization of cannabis brought about changes in legislation, business opportunities, public perception, and discussions surrounding drug policy.
